Description: Upper section of a pale green glazed composition female figure, naked with arms raised up, wearing elaborate wig, ears pierced, details incised and picked out in brown.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: San el-Hagar (Tanis), East of NW mounds, in Roman house
Curator's comments: Petrie, Tanis I, 38 See Favard-Meeks in Brissaud and Zivie-Coche: Tanis 1987-1997 (1998) p.120.
Bibliographic references: Bulté 1991 / Talismans égyptiens d'heureuse maternité : "faïence" bleu vert à pois foncés (no.94)
